<paragraph blockId="34.[144,758,781,865]" pageId="34" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis box="[144,269,781,802]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="533">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin word 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2011" box="[290,360,813,834]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nesocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis box="[290,360,813,834]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="533">nanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaning small, referring to the small size of the species.
</paragraph>
